1
00:00:24,230 --> 00:00:26,647
My mother was the first person in town
我媽媽是這個鎮上

2
00:00:26,747 --> 00:00:28,272
to die from the mold.
第一個死於黴病的

3
00:00:33,009 --> 00:00:36,339
It grew inside her lungs,and multiplied,
它在肺部裏成長而且日漸茁壯

4
00:00:36,487 --> 00:00:39,343
and made it difficult for her to breathe.
使她的呼吸變得困難

5
00:00:43,997 --> 00:00:48,267
For a short while she acted strange I guess.
有一段時間她的行徑變得很怪異，我想

6
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:52,000
Later, the mold spread to her brain,
後來，黴擴散到他的大腦

7
00:00:52,100 --> 00:00:54,634
and she died of a hemorrhage.
接著死於大量出血

8
00:00:55,982 --> 00:01:00,041
But, we didn't know that at the time.
但，那時我們並不知道

9
00:01:01,498 --> 00:01:05,401
At the time she was just dead.
她就這樣走了

10
00:01:34,778 --> 00:01:35,459
At first,
起初，

11
00:01:35,559 --> 00:01:38,659
the men in the white suits came from town.
穿著白套裝的男子從城鎮過來

12
00:01:39,873 --> 00:01:42,652
They took samples, and did tests,
他們取了樣本，做了測試

13
00:01:42,868 --> 00:01:45,616
and put everything into little plastic bags.
接著將所有東西裝入小塑膠袋裡

14
00:01:47,175 --> 00:01:49,081
Later, they took the chair
最後，他們將母親的座椅

15
00:01:49,181 --> 00:01:50,987
my mother died in to the dump
棄置在垃圾堆裡

16
00:01:51,060 --> 00:01:53,060
for the trash trucks to pick up.
任由垃圾車接走

17
00:01:54,232 --> 00:01:56,606
The man said it was infested.
男子說那是個寄生體

18
00:01:57,106 --> 00:01:59,106
That the mold had found a home
在黑暗又潮濕的布料中

19
00:01:59,138 --> 00:02:01,550
in the damp darkness of the fabric
黴病找到了歸屬

20
00:02:02,274 --> 00:02:04,809
and then spread to the rest of the house...
接著散播至房裡的各個角落

21
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:30,028
We had to pack what was left of our stuff
我們必須收拾其餘的個人物品

22
00:02:30,121 --> 00:02:32,143
and go live with my grandmother.
之後和祖母一起生活

23
00:02:34,191 --> 00:02:37,387
But even that was a false kind of peace.
那也只是偽裝的平靜

24
00:02:39,822 --> 00:02:40,668
The next day,
隔天

25
00:02:40,768 --> 00:02:43,071
a girl from down the road died,
住在街尾的女孩去世了

26
00:02:43,144 --> 00:02:44,636
and the night after that
再隔夜

27
00:02:44,708 --> 00:02:46,002
the whole Lawson family
整個Lawson家族

28
00:02:46,102 --> 00:02:47,396
passed away in their sleep.
在睡夢中死去

29
00:02:56,247 --> 00:02:58,562
The ambulance, and the men in white suits
救護車和白套裝的男子

30
00:02:58,662 --> 00:02:59,743
came again.
再度到來

31
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:03,242
They put more things in bags
將更多的物品裝進袋子裡

32
00:03:03,355 --> 00:03:05,933
and marked off the houses with yellow tape.
用黃色膠帶為房子做記號

33
00:03:07,919 --> 00:03:08,992
After that,
在那之後

34
00:03:09,492 --> 00:03:11,901
it was all anybody could talk about.
就成為大家口中唯一的話題

35
00:03:23,216 --> 00:03:24,236
At school,
學校裡

36
00:03:25,367 --> 00:03:28,455
the teachers showed us slides, and pictures,
老師用幻燈片撥放了一些照片

37
00:03:28,609 --> 00:03:30,609
and talked a lot about science,
並且說了許多關於科學研究的事

38
00:03:31,088 --> 00:03:32,295
but it didn't seem like
但他們似乎也並

39
00:03:32,395 --> 00:03:33,723
they understood it either.
不是完全很了解

40
00:03:35,588 --> 00:03:38,665
It was a rare and deadly kind of mold
黴病是一種罕見且致命的病

41
00:03:38,798 --> 00:03:40,979
and they weren't sure what caused it.
而他們其實也不確定是甚麼原因造成的

42
00:03:42,338 --> 00:03:45,471
They told us about a case once in Russia,
老師告訴我們一個在俄羅斯的案例

43
00:03:45,971 --> 00:03:47,868
where all these cows had died
那裡的牛全死了

44
00:03:48,918 --> 00:03:50,918
like, thousands of cows,
上千隻

45
00:03:51,662 --> 00:03:54,149
 and then everybody in the town died too
接著整座城鎮的人們跟著死亡

46
00:03:54,649 --> 00:03:56,649
because they didn't have enough to eat.
因為沒有足夠的食物能夠存活

47
00:03:58,228 --> 00:03:59,066
Later,
後來

48
00:03:59,709 --> 00:04:00,704
they figured it was
他們才發現

49
00:04:00,804 --> 00:04:02,426
something growing in the grass.
有東西在草裡擴長

50
00:04:07,101 --> 00:04:09,284
The preachers made a big deal of it,
傳教士們拿此大作文章

51
00:04:09,784 --> 00:04:11,355
and everybody went to church
使得所有人

52
00:04:11,455 --> 00:04:12,739
almost every day.
幾乎每一天都會去教堂

53
00:04:14,136 --> 00:04:15,700
They were always praying
總是祈禱著

54
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,922
and singing and hugging each other.
唱歌以及互相擁抱

55
00:04:19,624 --> 00:04:21,460
And outside of church,
然而在教堂外

56
00:04:21,960 --> 00:04:24,447
there was a lot of talk of other stuff too
對此有另外的說法

57
00:04:25,843 --> 00:04:28,113
If it was a curse of some kind,
說它其實是種詛咒

58
00:04:28,796 --> 00:04:30,492
or a hex.
或蠱惑

59
00:04:31,236 --> 00:04:32,876
A lot of people thought that
許多人認為這件事

60
00:04:32,976 --> 00:04:34,297
was what had happened,
就是這樣發生的

61
00:04:34,798 --> 00:04:37,318
and wondered who had brought it,
並揣測是誰引起

62
00:04:37,818 --> 00:04:39,737
and what had they done?
還有他們做了些甚麼

63
00:04:51,683 --> 00:04:53,807
Anyway, the mold came
總之，黴病侵入

64
00:04:53,818 --> 00:04:55,818
and the mold stayed.
且停駐

65
00:04:55,972 --> 00:04:57,972
The preachers couldn't pray it away,
傳教士門無法將它驅逐

66
00:04:58,207 --> 00:05:00,552
and the scientists couldn't figure it out.
科學家們也無從解釋

67
00:05:02,172 --> 00:05:04,400
They found it in kids backpacks,
黴病出現在小孩的背包上

68
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,411
and silverware drawers.
放餐具的抽屜裡

69
00:05:06,911 --> 00:05:08,911
People were going around in masks
群眾到哪都載著口罩

70
00:05:08,922 --> 00:05:11,289
like at the hospital all the time.
就像一直待在醫院一樣

71
00:05:12,278 --> 00:05:14,500
They said it floated around in the air
人們說它懸浮在空氣裡

72
00:05:14,578 --> 00:05:16,744
and that you could breathe it in.
你可能會將它呼吸至體內

73
00:05:19,382 --> 00:05:21,579
The days and hours passed like
那些日子和時間裡

74
00:05:21,679 --> 00:05:23,472
we were all underwater,
我們就像是被悶著

75
00:05:23,769 --> 00:05:25,005
or just walking around
或就像是一直用

76
00:05:25,105 --> 00:05:26,465
with cotton in our ears.
棉花將耳朵持續塞住

77
00:05:39,837 --> 00:05:42,806
But, every time we would go to the dump,
但，當每次我們去垃圾場

78
00:05:43,939 --> 00:05:45,939
there would be my mother's chair.
母親的座椅依然在那裏

79
00:05:46,990 --> 00:05:49,277
The trash trucks would come and go,
垃圾車來了又去

80
00:05:49,859 --> 00:05:51,408
and the chair would stay.
座椅仍在

81
00:05:53,235 --> 00:05:55,809
It was my grandmother who first noticed this,
祖母是第一個注意到這件事的人

82
00:05:56,615 --> 00:05:59,386
and later it became her obsession.
後來這件事就成了她的一種執念

83
00:06:00,346 --> 00:06:02,200
That perhaps the chair had brought
她認為就是那座椅

84
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:04,523
all of this darkness and suffering,
帶來了所有的邪惡和苦難

85
00:06:05,145 --> 00:06:07,370
and only the chair could take it away.
只有將座椅丟棄才能帶走這一切

86
00:06:09,871 --> 00:06:11,420
It got to the point where
這就是為什麼

87
00:06:11,430 --> 00:06:13,011
if the chair wasn't gone,
這張座椅並沒有被帶走的原因

88
00:06:13,368 --> 00:06:15,886
she would yell and scream at the trash lady,
她會對著收垃圾的女士怒吼、咆叫

89
00:06:16,386 --> 00:06:17,669
and curse her name.
並咒罵她

90
00:06:25,946 --> 00:06:26,570
To me,
對我來說

91
00:06:27,070 --> 00:06:28,438
it was just all part of a
這就只是

92
00:06:28,538 --> 00:06:30,425
kind of wildness in the world.
這世界裡失控的一小角

93
00:06:31,620 --> 00:06:33,727
The way the plants are always growing
如同植物攀

94
00:06:33,827 --> 00:06:35,181
all over everything
附生長上每件事物

95
00:06:35,417 --> 00:06:36,769
and taking it over.
直到顛覆掌控

96
00:06:37,494 --> 00:06:39,494
Like all the creatures all around,
像生長在大地上的所有物種

97
00:06:39,994 --> 00:06:42,345
just waiting on the edge of the woods
總是帶著黑暗與飢渴的眼神

98
00:06:42,498 --> 00:06:44,725
with their dark and hungry eyes.
躲藏在邊緣伺機行動

99
00:06:46,205 --> 00:06:49,000
There's bugs and things eating each other
昆蟲與其他生物獵殺著彼此

100
00:06:49,090 --> 00:06:50,720
and buzzing all around us.
殘殺的聲響環繞著我們

101
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,491
Even the air is at war with us,
甚至連空氣都參與了這場戰爭

102
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:57,440
rusting stuff all over
物件不斷的腐敗

103
00:06:57,695 --> 00:06:59,695
and eating it up from the inside.
並從內部蠶食個精光

104
00:07:07,339 --> 00:07:09,672
The papers talked all about wars,
報紙上提到的都是戰爭、

105
00:07:09,682 --> 00:07:10,831
and diseases,
疾病、

106
00:07:11,025 --> 00:07:12,389
and the dinosaurs,
與暴力

107
00:07:12,685 --> 00:07:14,685
and how they got wiped from the earth.
以及它們如何從這個地球上被抹滅

108
00:07:16,348 --> 00:07:18,203
How they were here one day,
又如何存在在這世上

109
00:07:18,642 --> 00:07:19,480
and then -
然後的然後

110
00:07:20,203 --> 00:07:21,020
poof.
砰

111
00:07:24,941 --> 00:07:26,542
We would play by the
我們會在夜晚時

112
00:07:26,642 --> 00:07:27,806
sometimes at night,
到水邊玩耍

113
00:07:28,634 --> 00:07:31,300
and we were always turning up old bottles
總會翻找出些舊瓶子

114
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,673
and stuff that nobody had ever seen before.
和一些從沒看過的東西

115
00:07:34,969 --> 00:07:38,169
Just old junk from some other civilizations,
其實也就只是些從其他文化地方來的老舊垃圾

116
00:07:38,853 --> 00:07:40,188
washed ashore in the mud
夾帶著泥

117
00:07:40,288 --> 00:07:41,910
with all the fiddler crabs.
和招潮蟹沖上岸

118
00:07:53,699 --> 00:07:56,613
My mother's funeral was postponed a while
母親的喪禮順延一陣子

119
00:07:56,786 --> 00:07:58,951
because they were studying her body,
因為他們再對她的身體做測試

120
00:07:58,982 --> 00:08:01,661
and analyzing its decomposition.
分析腐壞的部分

121
00:08:02,692 --> 00:08:05,419
The memorial service was in the winter,
追悼會是在冬季

122
00:08:05,654 --> 00:08:07,400
around the time of year
一年左右的時間

123
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,484
that everyone in town was burning leaves,
鎮上的每個人都在燃燒樹葉

124
00:08:09,841 --> 00:08:11,208
and the whole air
整個空氣就像又濕

125
00:08:11,308 --> 00:08:13,383
smelled like a wet, smoky dog.
又煙霧瀰漫的味道

126
00:08:18,477 --> 00:08:20,483
I think it was the smell that
我想是這些味道給了

127
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:21,745
gave me the idea,
我這個想法

128
00:08:23,001 --> 00:08:26,330
and then it was like I just knew,
接著它變成了我所熟知的味道

129
00:08:27,299 --> 00:08:29,911
or that I had known for a long time.
或者應該說是我早知道很久的味道了

130
00:08:31,472 --> 00:08:32,643
That she would not be
那她不會出

131
00:08:32,743 --> 00:08:34,004
at the memorial service.
現在追悼會

132
00:08:34,974 --> 00:08:37,217
That she would not be at the house.
不會出現在房子裡

133
00:08:38,556 --> 00:08:40,556
Even when I went to the dump,
即使是去垃圾場

134
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:43,061
I never expected to see that chair.
我都不再期待看見那張座椅

135
00:08:45,194 --> 00:08:46,689
How had she moved it,
他是如何搬走它的

136
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,267
all by herself?
全靠她一個人？

137
00:08:49,298 --> 00:08:51,898
Why did she take it to the water to burn?
她為什麼要搬去水邊焚燒？

138
00:08:53,194 --> 00:08:55,194
What was it about that chair?
這座椅到底有甚麼好追究的？

139
00:09:01,817 --> 00:09:03,335
It's been a long time
自從母親去世後

140
00:09:03,435 --> 00:09:04,845
since my mother died,
也過了好久

141
00:09:05,448 --> 00:09:06,773
but I still think about
但我依舊不時

142
00:09:06,873 --> 00:09:08,290
the strange black smoke
想起那詭異的黑煙

143
00:09:08,322 --> 00:09:09,949
coming up from that chair,
從座椅上漸漸升起

144
00:09:10,449 --> 00:09:12,088
filled with the mold
夾雜著黴

145
00:09:12,119 --> 00:09:13,482
that had infested it and
那侵擾著母親並深入

146
00:09:13,582 --> 00:09:15,236
burrowed into my mother's brain.
至她的大腦的黴病

147
00:09:21,534 --> 00:09:22,928
At that moment
那一剎那

148
00:09:23,428 --> 00:09:25,428
 I felt a kind of peaceful terror.
我感到一種平靜的恐懼感

149
00:09:27,622 --> 00:09:30,440
Was it in my body too, even then?
即使這樣它是否也存在在我體內？

150
00:09:31,512 --> 00:09:32,955
Growing in my lungs,
在肺部裡成長

151
00:09:32,986 --> 00:09:34,986
and making it's way to my eyes?
一路擴散到我的眼睛？

152
00:09:37,078 --> 00:09:38,500
I knew somehow
我知道無論如何

153
00:09:38,556 --> 00:09:39,890
that the troubles in our town
城鎮裡的困擾

154
00:09:39,990 --> 00:09:41,007
would soon be over,
很快就會結束的

155
00:09:41,508 --> 00:09:42,515
and in fact
然而事實上

156
00:09:42,668 --> 00:09:44,668
the mold did leave soon after,
之後黴病確很快地消失了

157
00:09:45,410 --> 00:09:46,962
never to return.
再也沒有出現過

158
00:09:49,503 --> 00:09:50,388
And yet,
然而

159
00:09:51,153 --> 00:09:53,710
part of me did not want this to be true.
一部分的我卻不希望這些是真的

160
00:09:54,924 --> 00:09:56,924
I wanted to breathe in the mold,
我希望在瀰漫著黴的空氣裡呼吸著

161
00:09:57,873 --> 00:09:59,278
just to know it.
了解它

162
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:02,086
To have it grow inside of me ...
讓他在我體內生長

163
00:10:03,137 --> 00:10:04,765
Over my eyes,
佈滿我的雙眼

164
00:10:05,181 --> 00:10:06,575
and my teeth,
和牙齒

165
00:10:07,176 --> 00:10:09,176
so that I would be in the ground
這樣一來我就會被埋進地底

166
00:10:09,227 --> 00:10:10,734
and become it ...
而成為它

167
00:10:11,683 --> 00:10:14,232
become a kind of mold myself
使自己成為一種黴

168
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:16,405
and then float through the air
飄散在空氣中

169
00:10:16,619 --> 00:10:18,619
and grow inside of you.
並在你身體裡茁壯

170
00:10:19,956 --> 00:10:23,871
Inside the wet, warm insides of your body,
濕潤又溫暖的體內

171
00:10:24,534 --> 00:10:27,060
until we were all the same thing.
直到我們都成為黴病為止
